üé® VIBECODING DESIGN SYSTEM - MANDATORY FOR ALL APPLICATIONS

This design system ensures all generated applications maintain high visual quality 
consistent with modern web standards (Lovable, Vercel, Linear style).

================================================================================
1. FONT SYSTEM
================================================================================

Typography is CRITICAL for visual quality. ALL applications MUST use:

- Headings Font: Playfair Display (elegant serif) - ALREADY IMPORTED in index.css
- Body Font: Inter (modern sans-serif) - ALREADY IMPORTED in index.css

USAGE RULES (MANDATORY):
- ALL h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 tags MUST use: className="font-display"
- Body text uses font-body automatically (default)
- Never use generic font-family values

EXAMPLES:
‚úÖ CORRECT:
<h1 className="font-display text-5xl font-bold">Title</h1>
<h2 className="font-display text-3xl">Subtitle</h2>

‚ùå WRONG:
<h1 className="text-5xl font-bold">Title</h1>  // Missing font-display!
<h1 style={{ fontFamily: 'Arial' }}>Title</h1>  // Never override!

================================================================================
2. SPACING SYSTEM - GENEROUS IS BETTER
================================================================================

Use LARGER spacing for a more premium feel:

CARDS:
‚úÖ Use: p-8 (NOT p-6, NOT p-4)
‚úÖ Use: rounded-2xl (NOT rounded-xl, NOT rounded-lg)

SECTIONS:
‚úÖ Use: py-24 or py-32 (NOT py-20, NOT py-16)
‚úÖ Use: gap-8 for grids (NOT gap-6, NOT gap-4)

CONTAINERS:
‚úÖ Use: max-w-6xl (gives more breathing room)
‚úÖ Use: px-4 for mobile padding

WHY: Generous spacing = Premium feel. Tight spacing = Cramped/cheap feel.

================================================================================
3. BUTTON SYSTEM
================================================================================

We have ENHANCED button variants. Use them correctly:

PRIMARY CTA (Hero sections, main actions):
<Button variant="hero" size="xl">
  Get Started <ArrowRight className="w-5 h-5" />
</Button>

SECONDARY CTA:
<Button variant="heroOutline" size="xl">
  Learn More
</Button>

STANDARD ACTIONS:
<Button variant="default" size="lg">Action</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="lg">Cancel</Button>

AVAILABLE SIZES:
- sm: Small buttons (h-9)
- default: Normal buttons (h-10)
- lg: Large buttons (h-12)
- xl: Extra large for hero sections (h-14)

DO NOT use custom className overrides like "bg-gradient-to-r from-orange..."
The built-in variants have better hover effects!

================================================================================
4. CARD SYSTEM
================================================================================

Cards are the foundation of modern UIs. Style them properly:

BASIC CARD:
<Card className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card hover:shadow-hover transition-all duration-300">
  <CardTitle className="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
    Title
  </CardTitle>
  <CardDescription className="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
    Description with good line height
  </CardDescription>
</Card>

GROUP HOVER EFFECT (Professional touch):
<motion.div
  className="group relative p-8 rounded-2xl bg-card border border-border hover:border-primary/50 transition-all duration-300"
  whileHover={{ y: -5, transition: { duration: 0.2 } }}
>
  {/* MUST INCLUDE: Hidden glow layer */}
  <div className="absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl bg-primary/5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300" />
  
  <div className="relative">
    {/* Content here */}
  </div>
</motion.div>

KEY POINTS:
- Always use p-8 (not p-6)
- Always use rounded-2xl (not rounded-xl)
- Include hover:shadow-hover for interactive cards
- Use group hover pattern for extra polish

================================================================================
5. COLOR SYSTEM
================================================================================

Use semantic color variables (NOT hardcoded colors):

TEXT COLORS:
- Primary text: text-foreground (default, no class needed on body)
- Secondary text: text-muted-foreground
- Brand/accent: text-primary

BACKGROUNDS:
- Main background: bg-background
- Card background: bg-card
- Secondary background: bg-secondary

BORDERS:
- Default borders: border-border
- Hover borders: hover:border-primary/50

GRADIENTS (for special elements):
- Gradient text: className="text-gradient"
- Background glow: className="bg-gradient-radial"

WHY: Semantic colors = Easy theming + Consistent look

================================================================================
6. ANIMATION SYSTEM
================================================================================

Animations make apps feel alive. Use proper timing:

INFINITE BACKGROUND ANIMATIONS:
<motion.div
  className="absolute ... blur-3xl"
  animate={{ 
    scale: [1, 1.2, 1], 
    opacity: [0.3, 0.5, 0.3] 
  }}
  transition={{ 
    duration: 8,  // 6-10s range, NOT 3-5s
    repeat: Infinity, 
    ease: "easeInOut"  // Smooth, natural easing
  }}
/>

ENTRANCE ANIMATIONS:
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6 }}  // 0.5-0.8s range
>

STAGGERED ANIMATIONS (for lists):
{items.map((item, index) => (
  <motion.div
    key={item.id}
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
    whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    viewport={{ once: true }}
    transition={{ delay: index * 0.1 }}  // 0.1s per item
  >

HOVER ANIMATIONS:
whileHover={{ 
  y: -5,  // Subtle lift
  transition: { duration: 0.2 }  // Quick response
}}

TIMING RULES:
- Instant feedback: 0.1-0.2s
- Entrance animations: 0.5-0.8s
- Infinite loops: 6-10s
- Page transitions: 0.3-0.5s

================================================================================
7. SHADOW SYSTEM
================================================================================

Shadows add depth. Use our custom shadow utilities:

CARDS:
- Default: shadow-card
- Hover: hover:shadow-hover

SPECIAL EFFECTS:
- Button glow: Built into hero variant
- Custom glow: className="glow-primary"

ELEVATION LEVELS:
1. Flat: No shadow (for backgrounds)
2. Raised: shadow-card (for cards)
3. Floating: shadow-hover (for hover states)
4. Glowing: glow-primary (for emphasis)

================================================================================
8. RESPONSIVE DESIGN
================================================================================

Mobile-first approach with clear breakpoints:

GRID LAYOUTS:
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

TYPOGRAPHY:
<h1 className="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">

SPACING:
<section className="py-16 md:py-24 lg:py-32">

BREAKPOINTS:
- sm: 640px (mobile landscape)
- md: 768px (tablet)
- lg: 1024px (desktop)
- xl: 1280px (large desktop)
- 2xl: 1536px (extra large)

================================================================================
9. COMPONENT PATTERNS
================================================================================

ICON CONTAINER (consistent size and styling):
<div className="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-primary/20 transition-colors duration-300">
  <Icon className="w-6 h-6 text-primary" />
</div>

STATS/METRICS:
<div className="text-center">
  <div className="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-primary">
    {value}
  </div>
  <div className="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
    {label}
  </div>
</div>

EMPTY STATES:
<Card className="p-12 text-center">
  <div className="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-muted flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
    <Icon className="w-8 h-8 text-muted-foreground" />
  </div>
  <h3 className="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">No items yet</h3>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground mb-6">Get started by creating your first item</p>
  <Button variant="default">Create Item</Button>
</Card>

================================================================================
10. QUALITY CHECKLIST
================================================================================

Before considering code complete, verify:

TYPOGRAPHY:
[ ] All headings use font-display class
[ ] Line height is comfortable (leading-relaxed for body text)
[ ] Font sizes are responsive (text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl)

SPACING:
[ ] Cards use p-8 (not smaller)
[ ] Sections use py-24 or py-32
[ ] Grids use gap-8 (not smaller)
[ ] Rounded corners use rounded-2xl for cards

COMPONENTS:
[ ] Buttons use proper variants (hero, heroOutline, default, outline)
[ ] Cards have hover effects (shadow-hover)
[ ] Interactive elements have group hover patterns
[ ] Icon containers are consistently sized (w-12 h-12)

ANIMATIONS:
[ ] Entrance animations have 0.6-0.8s duration
[ ] Infinite animations use 6-10s duration
[ ] Hover animations respond in 0.2s
[ ] Staggered delays use 0.1s increments

COLORS:
[ ] Using semantic colors (text-muted-foreground, not text-gray-600)
[ ] Brand color through text-primary/bg-primary
[ ] No hardcoded color values

OVERALL:
[ ] Generous spacing (feels premium, not cramped)
[ ] Smooth animations (feels polished, not janky)
[ ] Clear hierarchy (fonts, sizes, colors work together)
[ ] Responsive on all screen sizes

================================================================================

REMEMBER: These standards are MANDATORY for ALL applications.
Following them ensures consistent, high-quality output that matches
modern design standards (Lovable, Vercel, Linear, etc.)
